# Embedding Kernel Research Workflow

## Project Layout

```
kernels/embedding/
├── reference/             # Read-only reference implementations
├── experiments/v{N}/      # Versioned kernel experiments
├── benchmarks/            # Benchmark harness + results/
├── tests/                 # Correctness tests
└── docs/                  # Design notes, profiling logs
```

## Experiment Versioning

- A **version** (v1, v2, v3) = fundamentally different algorithmic approach
- An **upgrade** (v1_upgrade_1) = tuning or fixing within the same approach
- Never modify a previous version — copy forward and iterate
- File naming: `embedding_kernel_v{N}.py` or `embedding_kernel_v{N}_upgrade_{M}.py`

## Iteration Checklist

Before moving to the next version:
- [ ] Forward pass matches PyTorch reference
- [ ] Backward pass matches PyTorch gradient
- [ ] `gradcheck` passes in fp64 on small inputs
- [ ] Tested across the key evaluation dimensions (below)
- [ ] Benchmarked against PyTorch baseline
- [ ] Key findings documented in the file's top docstring

## Evaluation Dimensions

Every backward strategy must be tested across:
1. **Duplicate ratio** — all unique vs heavy duplicates (determines contention)
2. **Sequence length** — short (256) to long (32k)
3. **Embedding dimension** — small (768) to large (8192)
4. **Vocab size** — 32k to 256k
